body:
It would be helpful to know if the schema violation is from a plugin incompatibility with the new flat config or not, rather than user error, and therefore out of their hands.

The fact that it mentions  "plugins" in the error is somewhat helpful, but still somewhat confusing if you are switching to the flat config for the first time and have used a plugin like this:

```js
import plugin from 'some-plugin'

export default [
  plugin.configs.recommended,
  {
     plugins: { plugin }
  }
]
```

It is not immediately clear which `plugin` reference in the config the error message is referring to.

> I assume by "plugin compatibility" you mean if they're using the wrong config format?

Yep.

I bumped into this issue with `eslint-plugin-jest` and ended up reconfiguring their plugin in my flat config to make things work.

```js
import jest from 'eslint-plugin-jest'
import globals from 'globals'

jest.configs.recommended.plugins = { jest }
jest.configs.recommended.languageOptions = {
  globals: {
    ...globals.jest
  }
}
delete jest.configs.recommended.env

export  default [
   jest.configs.recommended,
   {
      plugins: { jest },
      languageOptions: {
        globals: { ...globals.jest }
     }
   }
]
```
